  "local_port": 53908,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I book a round trip on Uber such that it is counted as a single ride?",
  "response": "To book a round trip on Uber that is counted as a single ride, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open the Uber app** on your smartphone and make sure you are logged in to your account.\n\n2. **Enter your destination**: Tap on the \"Where to?\" field and enter the destination for the first leg of your trip.\n\n3. **Add a stop**: After entering your destination, tap on the \"+\" button or the \"Add Stop\" option (depending on your app version) to add your starting point as a stop. This will make your trip a round trip.\n\n4. **Reorder stops**: Make sure the stops are in the correct order. You should see your starting point as the first stop and your destination as the second stop. If needed, you can reorder them by holding and dragging the three lines next to each stop.\n\n5. **Confirm the trip**: Once you have set up your round trip, review the route and estimated fare. If everything looks good, tap \"Confirm\" or \"Request\" to book your ride.\n\n6. **Monitor the trip**: Your Uber driver will pick you up at your starting point and take you to your destination. Once you arrive at your destination, the app will automatically direct the driver to take you back to your starting point.\n\nKeep in mind that while this method will book a round trip, it may still be counted as two separate rides by Uber, depending on their policies and the specific details of your trip. If you have any questions or concerns, it's best to contact Uber support directly for clarification.",
